        <section class="- topic/section section" audience="expert" id="unique_3_Connect_42_dataserver_classic" nd:nd-id="dataserver_classic" importance="high" props="prop1"><h3 class="- topic/title title sectiontitle">DataServer - Classic</h3>
            
            
            
            <ul class="- topic/ul ul">
                <li class="- topic/li li"><p class="- topic/p p">vCPU: 4</p>
                    <p class="- topic/p p"> Even though increasing the number of vCPUs increases performance, the actual bene³ts depend on
                        whether the specific host is oversubscribed or not.</p></li>
                <li class="- topic/li li"><p class="- topic/p p">Memory: 16 GB</p>
                    <p class="- topic/p p"> While the minimum value works under light-load condition, as the load increases, the data server
                        quickly starts using swap space. For high load situations, increasing RAM beyond 16 GB can bene³t
